%N A395793 Decimal expansion of the principal moment of inertia of an oloid with unit mass density, formed by two unit circles, about the axis passing through the centers of the circles.
%C A395793 By choosing axes such that the origin is the midpoint of the line segment connecting the centers of the two circles and the x-axis passes through these centers, the moment of inertia tensor is diagonal. In this coordinate system, I_{xx} is equal to this constant, and I_{yy} = I_{zz} = A395794.
%H A395793 Robert Ferréol, <a href="https://www.mathcurve.com/surfaces.gb/orthobicycle/orthobicycle.shtml">Oloid</a>, MathCurve.
%H A395793 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.15145">The moment of inertia tensor of an oloid</a>, arXiv:2603.15145 [math.MG], 2026.
%H A395793 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CompleteEllipticIntegraloftheFirstKind.html">Complete Elliptic Integral of the First Kind</a>.
